                                    <span class="dot">2:30pm - 2:50pm</span>
                                </div>
                                <h4>Hristo Koshev</h4>
                                <p>Software Developer, Quanterall</p>
                                <div class="content-bio">
                                    <p>Hristo is a seasoned software developer, who started from procedural programming with Perl and PHP, passed through Object Oriented programming with Ruby and then his journey in programming continued with the functional programming lands of Elixir, Haskell, PureScript and Elm.</p> 
                                    <p>Currently, he is exploring Haskell Ivory tower, libraries and concepts and attempting to apply Category Theory to his day-to-day job.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <section class="l-v2-sdule-title">
                            <h4>Type Driven Functional Domain Modelling</h4>
                            <p>Hristo will show some of the ways we can use types as part of the design process. In particular, the thoughtful use of types can make a design more transparent and improve correctness at the same time.</p>
                            
                        </section>
